               <p>"Mrs. Bradshaw, who lives in <placeName id="t17710911-108-crimeloc582">Little Queen-Ann-street, Marybone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17710911-108-crimeloc582" type="placeName" value="Little Queen-Ann-street, Marybone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17710911-108-crimeloc582" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17710911-108-off579 t17710911-108-crimeloc582"></join>; deposed that her house was broke open on the 20th of June, that they were alarmed in the night, and that when she went down she found the area door and the kitchen window forced, and the things gone that are mentioned in the indictment".</p>
               <p>"Abigill Hatton, who is servant to Mrs. Bradshaw, deposed that she fastened the house over night, and that when she came down in the morning, she found the house broke open, and the things mentioned in the indictment gone."</p>
               <p>"
